Heat olive oil in 4-quart stockpot until it simmers. Add potatoes, leek, carrots and garlic, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender. Add chicken broth, tomatoes, green beans, kidney beans and pasta. Bring to a boil; simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until the pasta is cooked. Process garlic, basil and cheese in a food processor until a paste begins to form. Slowly add olive oil; process until combined. Season the soup to taste with salt and pepper. Serve the soup in bowls garnished with a spoonful of pistou.